		<!-- message -->
		<div>I have a couple questions actually- but low end stuff.<br />
<br />
I have a nicely-geared little necro twink (<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=672906" target="_blank">Cabdakin</a> - level 31) and I play him a few times a week when not on my main. Lately I've been either agro kiting in OT (big open space with evil outpost for the nasty gnome to sell trash loot and a PoK book in zone) or doing LDoN.<br />
<br />
1st question: are there better places for me to kite? I don't know that I'm the most efficient kiter in the world- generally I pet up, snare, stack dots to establish agro over pet melee and kite circles with Angus McBones smacking away from behind the mob. OT is good for this since it's a fairly unpopulated zone and the mob density is low enough that it's easy to kite and stay out of trouble.<br />
<br />
2nd question: LDoNs- what do other necros do? The mobs die so fast in LDoN (and any mobs at that level really) that dot stacking seems wasteful since only a couple rounds of damage will go in anyway. Typically I end up spending roughly half my time nuking/dotting (when i bother), a quarter of the time on CC duties for non-bard/chanter groups, and a quarter of the time pumping mana into my groupmates who are more often than not modestly geared (to be nice <img src="http://www.erollisimarr.com/styles/black/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Wink" class="inlineimg" /> ) in order to keep the group killing as fast as I prefer. Am I missing the boat on what to do here or is that about par for the course for necro-LDoNs?<br />
<br />
It's been a great class to play especially in groups that aren't that good- since I end up getting to pull, heal, tank, dot, nuke, and CC at various times and often all in the same 30 seconds. Was fun last night being the lowest level player in the group and taking 3 mobs after the 2 melees died. I won't ever be retiring Horm to play a necro fulltime, but I love playing this class- so much fun <img src="http://www.erollisimarr.com/styles/black/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" class="inlineimg" /></div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
